 4. Difference betweeen class attribute and id.
 A class attribute is a class name that can be used by multiple HTML elements.
 Example.
 <h2 class="city">Kuala lumpur.</h2>
 
 While an id is used by one HTML element.
 Example.
 <h2 id="R4">Row 4</h2>

